==English==
===Noun===
'''[[Olympic]] [[dive|diving]]'''
# A specific competition in the [[w:Olympics|Olympics]], involving [[diving]] off a ten-meter platform from a three-meter springboard.

===Quotations===
* '''2000,''' Timothy Vick, ''How to Pick Stocks Like Warren Buffett'' [http://print.google.com/print?hl=en&id=SWI1IkcuSDIC&pg=PA242&lpg=PA242&sig=SVXKH8tY7fNkHasGVkLlfHWWxTs]
*: Investors should remember that their scorecard is not computed using '''Olympic-diving''' methods: Degree-of-difficulty doesn’t count. 
* '''2002,''' Joseph L Badaracco Jr. ''Leading Quietly'' [http://print.google.com/print?hl=en&id=KOzUSxcXX20C&pg=PA117&lpg=PA117&sig=ny59AMgy0CgdsP8JLzrJFWrMDwc]:
*: Ethical efforts are often best judged like '''Olympic diving'''. It is important to compare what people actually accomplish to the degree of difficulty they face.
* '''2003,''' Michael Graham, ''Redneck Nation'' [http://print.google.com/print?hl=en&id=L2VDiFchxxcC&pg=PA209&lpg=PA209&sig=MfCAL4Sx4FWYmri2r0w6o1i8Kl0]
*: NASCAR on the radio is as stupid as '''Olympic diving''' on the radio: “Oooh, look at that splash—oh wait, you can’t. It’s on the radio.”